# Ordered Scope Map for the Agentic Software Framework

Yes. Think of the project as a set of **nested scopes**. The broadest scope is the full product. The narrowest scope is the single atomic commit we are working toward at any given moment.

```text
Product Scope
→ Repository Scope
→ Phase Scope
→ Workstream Scope
→ Work Packet Scope
→ Commit Scope
```

---

## 1. Product Scope — Entire Agentic Software Framework

This is the full product we are building.

The **Agentic Software Framework** is a repository-governed framework for disciplined AI-assisted software development.

It includes, ultimately:

```text
product/SDLC system
architecture and ADR governance
repository-based context continuity
work packets
verification model
repo contract testing
Foundry Control Plane
directive compiler and work protocols
evaluation harness
future runtime implementation
future retrieval/vector support
future tooling/CLI/app surfaces
future CI/dev workflow
future security and access controls
```

This is the **largest scope**.

Everything else is a smaller slice of this.

---

## 2. Repository Scope — The Current Repo as Source of Truth

The repository is the durable home for the framework.

The current repository scope includes:

```text
root governance files
product documents
architecture documents
ADR documents
domain documents
planning documents
verification documents
work-packet documents
AI/context-continuity documents
future source code
future scripts
future tests
future CI
future runtime implementation
```

Important rule:

```text
The uploaded repository tree is the active baseline.
```

That means we do **not** silently replace the repo with a cleaner imagined version. We move forward from the actual accepted tree.

