## 5. Work Packet Scope

This scope governs **how work gets done**.

Work packets are the atomic execution units of the project.

They live in:

```text
docs/work-packets/
```

A work packet defines:

```text
purpose
source inputs
scope
non-goals
assumptions
constraints
risks
affected files
implementation plan
acceptance criteria
verification plan
security/privacy notes
completion record
recommended atomic commit
follow-up work
```

The work-packet scope prevents us from doing vague, uncontrolled, mixed work.

